Description: Body fragment of a large closed vessel; streaky black glaze in lower part, reserved zone with bands in brown glaze above. Hard, fine, light orange clay, Munsell 5YR 7/6 (reddish yellow).
Findspot: Found/Acquired: Tell Dafana, Probably "Qasr", east annex (C), chamber 19 A, bench on west side
Curator's comments: Probably from the same vessel as BM GR 2010,5002.40, on which the Findspot number '19A W' is scratched
Bibliographic references: Weber 2012 / Untersuchungen zur archaischen griechischen Keramik aus anderen ägyptischen Fundorten (TD 349)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.208)
Acquisition notes: Found unregistered in the Department in 2010, in a box with other sherds from Tell Dafana.
